description:
The mutant warrior Cable is back from the dead – and he's planning on sending the Avengers to their graves! What's going on?! Don't you dare miss the shocking prelude to the epic Avengers versus X-Men saga!

By Jeph Loeb and Ed McGuinness.

Includes material reprinted from Avengers: X-Sanction

The operatives of the NOH learn that KABUKI has gone rogue and turned against thier directors. Each of the seven remaining NOH operatives is hot on her trail shaking down the underworld to find what became of Kabuki after her confrontation with KAI and then the NOH directors. Despite their protocol to remain masked and unknown to each other, some of the NOH agents learn secrets of the others in the hunt for Kabuki. Alliances are formed and loyalties are tested. The NOH track Kabuki to a secret government installation known as Control Corps. The NOH is concerned that Control Corps will debrief KABUKI and learn the secrets and history of the NOH. Kabuki is deemed a liability and the NOH operatives are given orders. Infiltrate the Control Corps instalation. Find Kabuki. If she dead, bring back her corpse. If she's alive... bring back her corpse.
name: Masks of the Noh

description: Kabuki finds herself in an institution for renegade government agents called Control Corps. It is a place where broken or defective government operatives are taken to be debriefed, psycho analyzed… and rebuilt, and reassigned if possible. With no Kabuki costume, and no mask to hide her scars, Kabuki finds herself in a psychological showdown with her interrogating analyst. Isolated, tormented, and only able to relate to the world through the security of her mask, her only comfort is a mysterious inmate named Akemi who sends inspirational notes that launch Kabuki to a new level of self-realization. Or is it just another trick?
name: Skin Deep

description: In an alternate-reality Japan, the masked female assassin known as Kabuki battles her former comrades in the Noh, who consider her a rogue. Following the events of Kabuki: Skin Deep, Kabuki is interviewed by a doctor at the Control Corps Hospital about her life so far. While following Akemi's lead, Kabuki reveals more about her traumatic childhood. Just as Kabuki is on the verge of a psychological breakthrough, the Noh assassins make their move. Kabuki battles the Noh assassins in the Hospital, as the ongoing Kabuki storyline that started with Skin Deep reaches a turning point.
name: Metamorphosis

person_credits.name: David Mack
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist, cover

description: We see the Noh's infiltration of the Control Corps facility from the POV of the NOH operative known as SCARAB. When the Noh shut down all the power and security systems of the facility, they inadvertantly released all of the inmates. As the Noh are overpowered and scattered by the freed inmates, Scarab attemps to find and help the Noh opperative TIGERLILY who she has clandestinely shared her civilian identity with.Scarab's complete story is shared, from her youth in the subcultures of urban Japan, awkward friendships, young romance, to her recruitment to the NOH, to her personal connection to Tigerlily. In Control Corps, Scarab runs into someone from her past. It is a life-changing event for her… and a possible new future awaits her… but will she sacrifice that to save TigerLily… and when she confronts KABUKI, will she do what she is ordered to?A fascinating shift in storytelling POV that shows Scarab as the protagonist and KABUKI as the obsticale. And when the dust clears… things are not the same.
name: Scarab: Lost in Translation

description: With the help of Akemi, KABUKI has escaped from Control Corps amidst all the fallout and mayhem. Walking through the rain, bleeding and wounded, She has been given a map to someone who will forge her a new passport and a way out of the country with a new identity.That person reveals more questions than answers concerning the nature of Akemi. Especially since that person thinks that Kabuki is Akemi. Having left her former life behind her, Kabuki has the chance to learn what her true calling in this life is. But it seems there is a kind of Akemi network. A network that Kabuki herself will be asked to help in. And it seems Akemi is attempting a kind of revolution. One that Akemi expects Kabuki to play a major part in. A revolution that will change the landscape of their world forever.
name: The Alchemy

The Fantastic Four's road trip through time and space continues! On an alien world, the team encounters a thousand-year-old prophecy: Is the Invisible Woman a long-awaited intergalactic messiah? Then, the F4 sightsee in ancient Rome and dine with Caesar on the Ides of March. Did somebody say, 'Pass the knife'? And it's a visit to both the beginning and the end of time, as Marvel's First Family witnesses the Big Bang and the Big Crunch! But to their surprise, they're not alone! What happens beyond the end of infinite time and space? Plus: One day a year, the Thing reverts to his human form. This year, Ben Grimm is going to go home again - as Ben Grimm! And when there's sibling rivalry between Franklin and Val, all bets are off! Collecting FANTASTIC FOUR (2012) #4-8.
name: Volume 2

description: An Avenger no more? In light of his recent violent actions, will the Avengers kick Spidey off the team? With a villain acting like a hero and a hero acting like a villain, one man has decided enough is enough! The ghostly revenant of Peter Parker fights to regain control of his body, his mind and his destiny! Is this the beginning of the end for Otto Octavius? The time has come to see who will live, who will die - and who will emerge as the one, true Superior Spider-Man! But when the Green Goblin returns, why is Spidey nowhere to be found? Plus: Jester! Screwball! Cardiac! And a new development for a Spider-Man who hasn't been seen for some time. And by 'time,' we mean centuries! Collecting SUPERIOR SPIDER-MAN #6-10.
name: Volume 2
